Miriam Rodriguez Martinez was known for successfully investigating the kidnapping and murder of her daughter by a drug cartel. CAPE TOWN - A Mexican businesswoman who was helping 600 families find kidnapped relatives has been murdered.Miriam Rodriguez Martinez was shot in her home in San Fernando.She was known for successfully investigating the kidnapping and murder of her daughter by a drug cartel.The information she gave police ensured the gang members were jailed.A colleague says she started receiving threats after one of the gang members escaped from prison two months ago.